getScheduledDurationOverrideValue() - Method in class com.ppm.integration.agilesdk.pm.ExternalTask
Upon work plan synchronization, PPM will automatically compute the task duration based on task start and finish dates, using the project regional calendar to account for non-working days.
If you do NOT want PPM to do that, make this field return a non-null duration value, and it will be used in the work plan.
Default value is null, meaning that PPM will automatically compute the duration.

linkTaskWithExternal(WorkPlanIntegrationContext, WorkplanMapping, ValueSet) - Method in class com.ppm.integration.agilesdk.pm.WorkPlanIntegration
Callback when a task is Mapped to an external application in the PPM work plan.
The WorkplanMapping object containing the linked task mapping configuration is passed to the method, and can be modified there before being returned, for example by adding extra config information that would only be generated in this callback method.
By default, this method does nothing and returns the WorkplanMapping object unmodified.
